This paper deals with the problem of discovering and removing discrimination in data science, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The use of causal networks and path-specific effects suggests that the paper is likely to be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on discrimination also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR), as well as social and information networks (cs.SI).
